1604814300.title: Bargain Hunt
1604814300.descr: Two teams of amateur antique collectors meet at an antiques fair to compete to make the largest profit from a three hundred pound budget. Once the contestants have done the shopping for their own items, the experts then take any leftover money and go shopping for more antiques which is 'bonus buys'. The teams then have to decide whether or not to take these items to auction.

1604829600.title: EastEnders

1604862900.title: Father Brown
1604862900.descr: Father Brown is a Catholic priest and an amateur detective solving murder cases, set during the 1950s in the fictional village Kembleford in Cotswold area, England. He uses his own wits as well as skills of his close friends, and being a priest allows him to look straight to the truth. He is strongly against the capital punishment for the capital crimes, as still applied in Britain of that time.

1604865600.title: The Split
1604865600.descr: Drama by award-winning writer Abi Morgan with a major role for Barry Atsma. Talented divorce attorney Hannah leaves her family's law firm to work for the competitor Noble & Hale. This puts the relationship with her mother Ruth and her sisters Nina and Rose under great pressure.

1604868900.title: Scott & Bailey
1604868900.descr: Follow personal and professional lives of Detectives Janet Scott and Rachel Bailey, members of the Major Incident Team- MIT, within the fictional Manchester Metropolitan Police who solve difficult cases and fight crime whilst risking their lives on a daily basis in order to help those in need.

1604871600.title: Rillington Place
1604871600.descr: The shocking true story of the serial killer John Christie is retold in this compelling three-part drama series. Directed by Craig Viveiros, the series chronicles the life of Christie, beginning with the break out of WWII and up to his execution, revealing the toxic marriage with his wife Ethel and the relationship he had with neighbour Timothy Evans. Featuring performances from Tim Roth, Nico Mirallegro, Samantha Morton, Jodie Comer and Eiry Thomas.
